&lt;&#x2F;h1&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-definition&quot; id=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;sup class=&quot;footnote-definition-label&quot;&gt;1&lt;&#x2F;sup&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provided that they are not &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;garbage collected&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; - Removing or modifying a package from the configuration doesn&#x27;t exactly delete older versions from the system. All they do is create a new derivation that no longer contains symlinks to the older packages. Since disk space is limited, unused packages should be removed at some point, which can be done using &lt;code&gt;nix-collect-garbage -d&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;nix store --gc&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
